2
00:00:14,054 --> 00:00:15,487
Stay loose.

3
00:00:28,902 --> 00:00:30,836
Hello?

4
00:00:30,904 --> 00:00:33,099
Anybody in there? Hello.

5
00:00:38,345 --> 00:00:39,778
Hi.

6
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:44,783
Right.

7
00:00:50,657 --> 00:00:53,524
- My turn? Do I go?
- Please.

8
00:00:53,594 --> 00:00:56,290
- The "bless me, Father" thing?
- Yes, my son.

9
00:00:56,363 --> 00:00:57,591
Right.

10
00:00:57,664 --> 00:01:00,599
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.
It's been...

11
00:01:02,636 --> 00:01:05,469
20, 25 years
since my last confession.

12
00:01:05,539 --> 00:01:09,908
I've used the Lord's name in vain
20, 30 times today.

13
00:01:14,014 --> 00:01:17,780
Okay. Where do I start?

14
00:01:19,486 --> 00:01:23,320
I've got a problem
that's causing me pain and heartache.

15
00:01:23,390 --> 00:01:25,358
Her name is Linda Paliski.

16
00:01:26,793 --> 00:01:31,196
She is everything.

17
00:01:31,265 --> 00:01:33,199
You know what I'm saying, Doc?

18
00:01:33,267 --> 00:01:35,633
Well, you wouldn't know
what I'm saying.

19
00:01:35,702 --> 00:01:39,297
But she's like...
How can I say it in your terms?

20
00:01:39,373 --> 00:01:42,638
She's my light, my beacon.

21
00:01:46,413 --> 00:01:48,347
My amazing grace.

22
00:01:48,415 --> 00:01:52,112
Look, changed man.
When can I move in?

23
00:01:54,354 --> 00:01:56,288
Do you have any dog food?

24
00:01:56,356 --> 00:01:59,951
Come on. How long
are those things good for?

25
00:02:00,027 --> 00:02:02,427
- I'll get you what I have.
- I'll come up and get it.

26
00:02:02,496 --> 00:02:04,327
No, you won't.

27
00:02:04,398 --> 00:02:07,765
Is this going to be a permanent thing,
because I gave Blinker to you.

28
00:02:07,834 --> 00:02:10,428
We're sort of like apart now.

29
00:02:10,504 --> 00:02:13,496
She's dumped me.

30
00:02:15,275 --> 00:02:17,505
This is Rhonda.
What do you want?

31
00:02:17,577 --> 00:02:19,704
How courteous. It's me, Gary.

32
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:22,613
Linda wants me to come up
and get some dog food.

33
00:02:22,683 --> 00:02:24,617
Hold on.

34
00:02:24,685 --> 00:02:26,983
Great, Blinkie.
Me and you, baby.

35
00:02:29,423 --> 00:02:33,325
The thing that really
gets to the problem...

36
00:02:33,393 --> 00:02:35,588
is that I'm in sales.

37
00:02:35,662 --> 00:02:37,425
It's not sales.

38
00:02:37,497 --> 00:02:41,263
It's resales. I'm a scalper.

39
00:02:41,335 --> 00:02:43,098
I'm a ticket scalper.

40
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:48,130
I'm a scalper, for chrissakes.
That's why she dumped me.

41
00:02:48,208 --> 00:02:51,143
It's been two months, and she hasn't
directed one word towards me.

42
00:02:51,211 --> 00:02:53,338
Even a look in my direction.

43
00:02:53,413 --> 00:02:57,349
I'd like to do the right thing.
I'd like to get a legit gig.

44
00:02:57,417 --> 00:03:00,147
But those things are like another world.
Are you getting this?

45
00:03:00,220 --> 00:03:02,450
Because it doesn't stop there.

46
00:03:02,522 --> 00:03:05,719
I've got this guy that works for me.
He's my holder.

47
00:03:05,792 --> 00:03:08,283
Talk about carrying the cross.

48
00:03:08,362 --> 00:03:10,796
You got mustard on your chin, Benny.

49
00:03:11,999 --> 00:03:13,432
Tell me something.

50
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:17,095
- You seen any oscars today?
- Nope. Haven't seen a cop all morning.

51
00:03:17,170 --> 00:03:20,071
- Benny, who's that?
- What?

52
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:22,802
That guy over there.
Uniform. Hat.

53
00:03:22,876 --> 00:03:24,741
Badge.

54
00:03:24,811 --> 00:03:29,248
That's another navy blue.
I should've seem him.

55
00:03:29,316 --> 00:03:31,910
Can we pay attention here?
I'm trying to work.

56
00:03:31,985 --> 00:03:34,112
I'm on it, Chief. I'm with you.

57
00:03:34,187 --> 00:03:38,487
I'm gonna do such a good job for you
'cause I love you so much.

58
00:03:38,558 --> 00:03:41,891
And I'm just here,
I'm just paralyzed.

59
00:03:41,962 --> 00:03:45,454
I just need...
I just want a little guidance.

60
00:03:45,532 --> 00:03:48,626
Just a little something.
Gimme a sign.

61
00:03:48,702 --> 00:03:52,035
A little light at the end of the tunnel.
Something to hang my hat on.

62
00:03:52,105 --> 00:03:55,131
Recognizing your problem
is half the battle, my son.

63
00:03:55,208 --> 00:03:57,142
Find a new path to travel.

64
00:03:57,210 --> 00:03:59,178
Follow your heart.
Do God's work.

65
00:03:59,246 --> 00:04:02,147
The strength is within you.
Find the courage.

66
00:04:02,215 --> 00:04:04,149
What, are you in a hurry?

67
00:04:05,986 --> 00:04:07,851
God will show you the way.

68
00:04:07,921 --> 00:04:11,379
I'm here for the "how" part. How?

69
00:04:11,458 --> 00:04:13,653
You know, the light, the vision.

70
00:04:13,727 --> 00:04:15,922
As I said, God will show you the way.

71
00:04:15,996 --> 00:04:18,430
Trust in Him.
You'll find strength in Him.

72
00:04:18,498 --> 00:04:20,432
Go in peace, my son.

73
00:04:21,635 --> 00:04:25,332
But before you do, you have any tickets
for the Knicks' game Friday night?

74
00:04:29,276 --> 00:04:31,801
Sold out.
I got two tickets.

75
00:04:31,878 --> 00:04:37,578
Van Gogh Ear ashtrays!
$10, two for $20. What a deal.

76
00:04:37,651 --> 00:04:40,814
It's sold out.
30 bucks apiece.

77
00:04:40,887 --> 00:04:42,320
Knock yourself out.

78
00:04:42,389 --> 00:04:45,017
I'd like a refund.
I didn't enjoy the show.

79
00:04:45,092 --> 00:04:47,526
I can't give you a refund.
I didn't produce the show.

80
00:04:47,594 --> 00:04:50,893
Gary, tell the lady
we don't give refunds.

81
00:04:50,964 --> 00:04:54,092
Refunds? We got refunds.
The guy in the red hat.

82
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:57,295
I'm sorry. The guy in the red hat.

83
00:04:57,370 --> 00:05:00,862
You can talk to him over there.
Good luck. We'll see you next year.

84
00:05:02,109 --> 00:05:05,567
Take the tickets to Mrs. Manhime.
Pick up $200.

85
00:05:05,645 --> 00:05:09,672
- Manhime. M-A-N-H-l-M-E.
- I got it.

86
00:05:09,749 --> 00:05:14,049
Come on. Oyster Perpetual!
El Presidente. Submariners.

87
00:05:14,121 --> 00:05:17,420
They're releasing tickets for tonight
at the Meadowlands.

88
00:05:17,491 --> 00:05:21,257
We're making a move to Jersey.
Pick up those tickets at will-call.

89
00:05:21,328 --> 00:05:25,025
And see Mrs. Manhime
and collect $200.

90
00:05:25,098 --> 00:05:26,565
Let's go.

91
00:05:27,701 --> 00:05:30,192
- How you feeling?
- I'm okay. Just hate this business.

92
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:32,261
Go. You got it.

93
00:05:41,214 --> 00:05:44,706
I'm gonna hang around here,
mop up the museum. I don't wanna go.

94
00:05:44,784 --> 00:05:47,947
Are you crazy? The joint's
almost closed. No one can sell a ticket.

95
00:05:48,021 --> 00:05:50,489
- Get on the bus.
- I'll take whatever you got, half face.

96
00:05:50,557 --> 00:05:56,086
You got it. Here you go.
Come back. You're crazy.

97
00:05:56,163 --> 00:06:00,532
Save me some tickets, all right?
Okay. We'll see ya.

98
00:06:09,075 --> 00:06:12,374
Arigato, fellow-san!

99
00:06:12,445 --> 00:06:15,005
Got tickets.

100
00:06:25,659 --> 00:06:28,594
Yes, American tickets.

101
00:06:28,662 --> 00:06:30,323
Big American scalper.

102
00:06:57,691 --> 00:07:00,057
How many more tickets
did Gary sell than you?

103
00:07:00,126 --> 00:07:03,152
And how many T-shirts and watches
did you have to pedal home?

104
00:07:03,230 --> 00:07:04,663
A couple.

105
00:07:13,173 --> 00:07:15,641
- Where's the food?
- It's coming.

106
00:07:19,179 --> 00:07:21,113
Hey, the man!

107
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:26,084
How you doing, Professor?

108
00:07:28,221 --> 00:07:30,781
You consider my proposition?

109
00:07:30,857 --> 00:07:32,290
I did.

110
00:07:32,359 --> 00:07:34,054
And?

111
00:07:35,729 --> 00:07:37,321
Hello!

112
00:07:37,397 --> 00:07:42,357
It's the thing about working alone.
That's the way I gotta do this.

113
00:07:44,204 --> 00:07:48,436
I mean, it's no offense to...
It's the way I have to do this.

114
00:07:48,508 --> 00:07:50,533
Why don't you relax?

115
00:07:50,610 --> 00:07:53,704
I'll do that. Okay.

116
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:56,681
This is not a shakedown.
This is just a business idea.

117
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:59,583
- You make me nervous.
- We're all adults here.

118
00:08:02,455 --> 00:08:04,389
Give this to Sylvia when she comes in.

119
00:08:09,396 --> 00:08:12,593
- What was that about?
- Barry the Book.

120
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:14,634
Bookmaker to the degenerates.

121
00:08:14,701 --> 00:08:18,000
Wants to buy a piece of me,
stake me financially for a percentage.

122
00:08:18,071 --> 00:08:21,700
- You know what that means.
- Gary, you don't need anybody.

123
00:08:21,775 --> 00:08:24,141
The museum today? You're a god.

124
00:08:27,113 --> 00:08:30,412
- Good call, brother.
- Good call, that's it.

125
00:08:30,483 --> 00:08:32,474
Anybody hear anything
about the pope today?

126
00:08:32,552 --> 00:08:36,579
- What pope?
- Big guy. Tall. White hair. Long dress.

127
00:08:36,656 --> 00:08:41,559
My sources tell me it's between
New York, Moscow or Russia.

128
00:08:41,628 --> 00:08:46,258
Acts don't go to Siberia when they can
come to the media capital of the world.

129
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,267
The Big Apple.

130
00:08:49,602 --> 00:08:53,561
I hear the stadium's holding open dates.
Rescheduling events.

131
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,403
End of the month.

132
00:08:55,475 --> 00:08:56,908
You heard that?

133
00:08:56,976 --> 00:08:59,240
You really think he'll come here?

134
00:09:00,313 --> 00:09:02,508
I pray every night that he does.

135
00:09:02,582 --> 00:09:05,016
An event like this is like...

136
00:09:05,085 --> 00:09:07,952
- Comes around once in a lifetime.
- And lives get changed.

137
00:09:08,021 --> 00:09:10,489
- What did you say?
- And lives get changed.

138
00:09:43,623 --> 00:09:46,990
How you doing, Blink?
Move over.

139
00:09:47,060 --> 00:09:50,120
We better call Lin.
Wanna call Lin?

140
00:10:06,546 --> 00:10:09,276
Hi, it's Linda.
I'm not here to take your call.

141
00:10:09,349 --> 00:10:12,477
Leave a message after the tone.
Bye.

142
00:10:12,552 --> 00:10:16,454
Hi, Linda.
It's me, the asshole.

143
00:10:16,523 --> 00:10:19,253
I know you're there.
Will you pick up, please?

144
00:10:19,325 --> 00:10:21,850
Come on, baby.
I need to talk to you.

145
00:10:23,563 --> 00:10:26,054
Okay, I'll just talk to you then.

146
00:10:26,132 --> 00:10:29,568
How are things doin'?
Everything's well?

147
00:10:31,738 --> 00:10:34,070
Come on, please.
I've gotta talk to you.

148
00:10:34,140 --> 00:10:37,166
I wouldn't be calling if it
wasn't important. Please pick up.

149
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:43,446
Okay, I'm going to stop by
the store tomorrow.

150
00:10:43,516 --> 00:10:45,381
All right, okay.

151
00:10:45,452 --> 00:10:48,046
You know what? If you don't pick up
in five seconds...

152
00:10:48,121 --> 00:10:50,521
I'll take that as a yes
and I'm coming tomorrow.

153
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:52,182
One, two, three, four, five.

154
00:11:08,641 --> 00:11:11,371
This set is really great
for the kitchen.

155
00:11:11,444 --> 00:11:15,710
