that you're here without your wife...

184
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:56,510
and couldn't make a decision
without her.

185
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:58,744
This is an extraordinary
piece of equipment.

186
00:12:58,818 --> 00:13:03,585
This equipment was designed
for only the most deserving of men.

187
00:13:03,656 --> 00:13:06,056
The working man.

188
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,685
The man who is the backbone
of this country.

189
00:13:08,761 --> 00:13:13,858
A man who deserves not 13",
but the full 60" experience.

190
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:16,595
Full visual stimulus,
a cacophony of sound...

191
00:13:16,669 --> 00:13:19,866
that stimulates the ocular nerve.

192
00:13:19,939 --> 00:13:22,203
Have you ever had
your ocular nerve stimulated?

193
00:13:23,443 --> 00:13:24,876
Yeah, once.

194
00:13:24,944 --> 00:13:29,381
An assault on the senses. It takes you
to a place where everything is good.

195
00:13:29,449 --> 00:13:32,612
Where everything's swell.

196
00:13:32,685 --> 00:13:36,086
But, again,
your wife is not here.

197
00:13:37,457 --> 00:13:40,255
Oh, goodness. Can l...

198
00:13:43,296 --> 00:13:45,264
What?

199
00:13:45,331 --> 00:13:47,265
No, you'd better leave.

200
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:49,733
- Why?
- This is a private thing.

201
00:13:49,802 --> 00:13:51,736
What are you talking about?

202
00:13:51,804 --> 00:13:56,036
- You never entered the "Stargate"?
- No. Have I missed something?

203
00:13:56,109 --> 00:13:58,077
Take a load off.

204
00:14:03,750 --> 00:14:07,151
The first time I went through
the "Stargate"...

205
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:09,688
it was an extraordinary experience
I never forgot it.

206
00:14:09,756 --> 00:14:11,724
And you'll never forget me.

207
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:13,224
Here we go.

208
00:14:14,227 --> 00:14:17,253
Look at that baby.
Just push "play"...

209
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:18,820
and we're off.

210
00:14:21,167 --> 00:14:22,600
Here we go.

211
00:14:22,669 --> 00:14:24,330
He's a good actor.

212
00:14:24,404 --> 00:14:28,568
Just relax. Let yourself go.
Go with the feel.

213
00:14:28,641 --> 00:14:30,905
Go with the sound, with the feeling.

214
00:14:45,391 --> 00:14:47,086
You're there. You own it.

215
00:14:49,595 --> 00:14:52,325
You're on. See?

216
00:14:52,398 --> 00:14:54,423
What a rush.

217
00:14:57,904 --> 00:15:01,237
- How much is it?
- How much is this?

218
00:15:01,307 --> 00:15:04,936
Not any more than what you spend
on your wife for manicures, pedicures...

219
00:15:05,011 --> 00:15:07,536
facials, hair dying...

220
00:15:07,613 --> 00:15:10,047
and tennis lessons
with that 20-year-old pro.

221
00:15:10,116 --> 00:15:12,209
What do you get out of that?

222
00:15:12,285 --> 00:15:14,150
Zero.

223
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:18,384
For $99 a month,
in about 18 years you get that.

224
00:15:19,559 --> 00:15:22,027
That TV right there.

225
00:15:22,095 --> 00:15:23,858
Enjoy your TV.

226
00:15:28,401 --> 00:15:30,562
Okay, you win.
Listen good and hard.

227
00:15:30,636 --> 00:15:32,831
Pick me up at 8:00.
Not 8:01.

228
00:15:32,905 --> 00:15:35,806
Pope John Paul will make his awaited
State of the World address...

229
00:15:35,875 --> 00:15:37,809
here in New York City
at Yankee Stadium...

230
00:15:37,877 --> 00:15:40,038
two weeks from this Sunday.

231
00:15:40,113 --> 00:15:42,081
The pope last visited the United States
over six years ago.

232
00:15:42,148 --> 00:15:44,616
The visit comes as a bit of a surprise.

233
00:15:44,684 --> 00:15:46,743
- Do you hear me?
- Thank you so much.

234
00:15:46,819 --> 00:15:48,013
Yes!

235
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:51,818
Lordy, Lordy! My Lord, my Savior.
Hallelujah.

236
00:15:51,891 --> 00:15:55,622
It's just dinner.
It's not gonna be that exciting.

237
00:15:55,695 --> 00:15:59,563
I have some things to tell you,
so if you show up one nanosecond late...

238
00:15:59,632 --> 00:16:02,032
Not more "ifs," no more "buts."

239
00:16:02,101 --> 00:16:03,534
No more "maybes."

240
00:16:03,603 --> 00:16:06,572
Thank you.
You're so beautiful.

241
00:16:08,241 --> 00:16:10,004
I'll see ya.

242
00:16:10,076 --> 00:16:12,977
8:00, Linda Paliski's.

243
00:16:13,045 --> 00:16:15,411
With my shiny shoes on.

244
00:16:21,587 --> 00:16:24,420
Make sure you get diggers, and tell them
it's gonna be an overnighter.

245
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:27,152
After that, check all
the local churches...

246
00:16:27,226 --> 00:16:29,660
Salvation Army...

247
00:16:29,729 --> 00:16:32,459
the Red Cross, choirs,
anybody who's connected.

248
00:16:32,532 --> 00:16:34,523
What do you think?
"He's back."

249
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:37,933
- Or "Yo, Pope, over here."
- "Yo, Pope, over here."

250
00:16:39,505 --> 00:16:41,302
"He is here."

251
00:16:41,374 --> 00:16:43,808
Stinko. Stick to tickets.
Zeus, what are you working on?

252
00:16:45,344 --> 00:16:46,936
Popesicles.

253
00:16:47,013 --> 00:16:52,144
Pontiff Purple, Roman Raspberry
and Christian Cherry.

254
00:16:52,218 --> 00:16:55,619
- Tony, cut him off quick.
- No more shrimp for you.

255
00:16:55,688 --> 00:16:58,816
- You're going to ruin my picture.
- He is here

256
00:16:58,891 --> 00:17:01,325
The pope is here

257
00:17:01,394 --> 00:17:03,988
Bong
We're in the money

258
00:17:11,504 --> 00:17:13,438
Hey, Gary, what's the word?

259
00:17:13,506 --> 00:17:16,407
The word is pope tickets. I'm paying
five over face value. No limit.

260
00:17:16,475 --> 00:17:18,909
I'll take everything you can get
your tiny hands on.

261
00:17:22,048 --> 00:17:24,846
- Make it 10 over face.
- Ten over face?

262
00:17:24,917 --> 00:17:26,248
You heard me.

263
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:28,753
What do they teach you in here?

264
00:17:30,122 --> 00:17:31,783
Okay, ten. Deal.

265
00:17:31,858 --> 00:17:34,452
Stanley, take your diggers
to Yankee Stadium tomorrow...

266
00:17:34,527 --> 00:17:36,893
and get me as many pope tickets
as you can.

267
00:17:36,963 --> 00:17:39,056
I'll pay ten over face, no limit.

268
00:17:40,066 --> 00:17:42,000
I need these tickets badly.

269
00:17:43,970 --> 00:17:46,803
Close the parking lot.
You owe me.

270
00:17:46,873 --> 00:17:50,331
What are you saying, Arty?
I need pope tickets.

271
00:17:50,409 --> 00:17:53,344
I got nothin' for ya.

272
00:17:53,412 --> 00:17:57,007
Sold your allotment to some new guy.
Walked up where you're standing now.

273
00:17:57,083 --> 00:17:59,813
Offered me double your grease.
I should say no to that?

274
00:17:59,886 --> 00:18:02,753
You should say, "Wait a minute,"
and call me.

275
00:18:02,822 --> 00:18:05,290
It's two years
we've had this arrangement.

276
00:18:05,358 --> 00:18:08,725
If you're unhappy, all you gotta do
is say something. We'll work it out.

277
00:18:08,794 --> 00:18:10,887
You couldn't beat the offer.

278
00:18:10,963 --> 00:18:12,954
Besides, it was cash on the spot.

279
00:18:13,032 --> 00:18:15,193
- Who was it?
- Some new guy.

280
00:18:15,268 --> 00:18:17,702
Never saw him before.
Slick, though.

281
00:18:17,770 --> 00:18:22,400
Cell phone. Beeper.
Had an island accent.

282
00:18:29,048 --> 00:18:31,915
How you doing, Benny?

283
00:18:31,984 --> 00:18:34,043
Who's this guy?

284
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:37,180
Check it out, Johnny.
The Cheshire Cat.

285
00:18:37,256 --> 00:18:39,690
It's some island guy from Miami.
Showed up a couple days ago.

286
00:18:39,759 --> 00:18:41,693
We talked for a minute.

287
00:18:44,096 --> 00:18:45,586
We talked.

288
00:18:52,305 --> 00:18:54,637
Let me call you back.

289
00:18:57,576 --> 00:18:59,771
How you doing, man?

290
00:18:59,845 --> 00:19:01,506
Gary, right?

291
00:19:01,580 --> 00:19:04,105
Heard a lot about you.
Casino.

292
00:19:07,453 --> 00:19:09,785
Go by the Broadhurst today?

293
00:19:09,855 --> 00:19:13,552
Yeah, man. Picked up
some nice action over there, boy.

294
00:19:16,562 --> 00:19:18,860
Casino here.
How many you need?

295
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:23,633
Broadhurst is my juice.
Has been.

296
00:19:23,703 --> 00:19:26,399
- Arty's your connection?
- That's right.

297
00:19:26,472 --> 00:19:28,702
- I didn't know he was greased already.
- Now you know.

298
00:19:28,774 --> 00:19:30,969
This is a problem.
No, no. No problem.

299
00:19:31,043 --> 00:19:32,567
Gary, let's go.

300
00:19:32,645 --> 00:19:36,911
It's a quarter to. You got to get
yourself presentable for Linda tonight.

301
00:19:38,084 --> 00:19:40,450
- You gotta be sharp for Linda.
- I got you.

302
00:19:40,519 --> 00:19:42,714
Sorry. So you were saying?

303
00:19:42,788 --> 00:19:45,018
I said, undo what you did.

304
00:19:45,091 --> 00:19:48,618
Next time check things out,
otherwise we're gonna have a problem.

305
00:19:48,694 --> 00:19:49,991
Otherwise?

306
00:19:51,297 --> 00:19:53,424
Shit happens, bro.

307
00:19:53,499 --> 00:19:57,299
This is the wild west. There are
no rules. This is a day-by-day thing.

308
00:19:57,370 --> 00:19:59,702
You slick, smiling shyster.

309
00:19:59,772 --> 00:20:02,502
You don't tell him what to do.
He tells you.

310
00:20:02,575 --> 00:20:04,736
- Get him out of here. Pull the punch.
- I'll drop him so fast.

311
00:20:04,810 --> 00:20:07,677
- Take him out of here.
- He won't know up from down.

312
00:20:07,747 --> 00:20:09,180
Let's go, champ.

313
00:20:10,883 --> 00:20:12,316
Oh, Jesus.

314
00:20:13,252 --> 00:20:14,685
Business is heating up.

315
00:20:14,754 --> 00:20:16,745
Talk to me later.

316
00:20:16,822 --> 00:20:19,450
We'll work something out.

317
00:20:22,194 --> 00:20:24,162
- Count on it.
- Right.

318
00:20:26,899 --> 00:20:30,494
He tries that again, I'll drill fingers
in his head, use it as a bowling ball.

319
00:20:30,569 --> 00:20:32,298
Know what I mean?

320
00:20:32,371 --> 00:20:35,238
Hey, Gary, swag sale.
Do you want a coat?

321
00:20:35,307 --> 00:20:37,468
TV? Cigars? Batteries?

322
00:20:37,543 --> 00:20:39,534
- Fat fuck!
- Fuck you!

323
00:20:40,813 --> 00:20:43,179
I'd rather swallow Clorox
than deal with Fat Max.

324
00:20:43,249 --> 00:20:44,876
Scum of the earth.

325
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:47,544
Draws no lines. Today it's coats,
tomorrow it's something else.

326
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:50,316
- Know what I mean?
- Yeah.

327
00:20:57,430 --> 00:20:59,364
Are you clean?

328
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:03,235
Yeah, Gary.

329
00:21:03,302 --> 00:21:05,236
I would never let you down.

330
00:21:06,806 --> 00:21:09,673
I appreciate what you've done for me.
It's been two years.

331
00:21:12,678 --> 00:21:14,737
You're a good kid.

332
00:21:14,814 --> 00:21:17,078
Somebody's gonna have to take over
when I retire.

333
00:21:17,149 --> 00:21:19,140
You will never retire.

334
00:21:19,218 --> 00:21:21,152
As most of you are aware...

335
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:24,451
Miss Bennett is the restaurant critic
for the New York Times.

336
00:21:24,523 --> 00:21:26,650
Her palate is exquisite.

337
00:21:26,725 --> 00:21:30,627
And her review will count for one-third
of your total grade this quarter.

338
00:21:30,696 --> 00:21:34,996
You will be judged on taste,
texture and presentation.

339
00:21:36,268 --> 00:21:39,897
Medallion de veau en croute?

340
00:21:39,972 --> 00:21:42,634
Very ambitious, my dear.

341
00:21:44,677 --> 00:21:46,611
It's a lovely presentation.

342
00:21:54,487 --> 00:21:56,421
It's very well done.

343
00:22:11,937 --> 00:22:17,136
It's obvious you possess
a very rare talent, my dear.

344
00:22:18,277 --> 00:22:21,974
I would like to see
more of your cooking.

345
00:22:47,506 --> 00:22:48,939
Nice and cool.

346
00:22:51,277 --> 00:22:53,211
You're the man.

347
00:22:59,652 --> 00:23:01,085
Who's there?

348
00:23:02,855 --> 00:23:04,288
Gary?

349
00:23:05,457 --> 00:23:06,890
You're back.

350
00:23:07,726 --> 00:23:10,627
How are you, Mrs. D.?
You're looking well.

351
00:23:10,696 --> 00:23:13,859
And you need glasses. Wait.

352
00:23:15,801 --> 00:23:18,395
Give this back to Julia Child.

353
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:22,634
Tell her I couldn't even tell
it was goat. Tasted just like chicken.

354
00:23:22,708 --> 00:23:24,141
Will do.

355
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,948
You ever spend time
in your own apartment, Rhonda?

356
00:23:31,016 --> 00:23:34,042
What for? It's more fun here
watching you suffer.

357
00:23:34,119 --> 00:23:37,850
- Linda, Dean Martin is here.
- Very funny.

358
00:23:37,923 --> 00:23:40,585
Here, lick the plate.

359
00:23:45,664 --> 00:23:48,360
She's testing cookbooks again...

360
00:23:48,434 --> 00:23:50,368
so I'm gaining like a sponge.

361
00:23:52,204 --> 00:23:54,832
She's been fussing all day.

362
00:23:56,075 --> 00:23:57,508
Really?

363
00:23:59,178 --> 00:24:02,079
I think I'm gonna go.
I can't bear to watch this.

364
00:24:02,147 --> 00:24:04,240
Good.

365
00:24:04,316 --> 00:24:07,410
I'm going downstairs
to try to get a taxi.

366
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:13,754
I'm sorry.
I tried to call you three times.

367
00:24:15,728 --> 00:24:17,161
Not Mrs. Haywood?

368
00:24:17,229 --> 00:24:20,255
Mrs. Haywood, but no notice
and an impossible menu.

369
00:24:20,332 --> 00:24:22,994
Oh, flowers. Oh, Blink.

370
00:24:24,303 --> 00:24:25,736
Asparagus.

371
00:24:25,804 --> 00:24:28,864
Haywood time! Blinkie, lay down.
Stay calm. We can do this.

372
00:24:28,941 --> 00:24:31,432
I've got the water. Here we go.

373
00:24:31,510 --> 00:24:34,001
- This is such a big break for me.
- I see that.

374
00:24:34,079 --> 00:24:36,013
I'm really nervous.

375
00:24:37,116 --> 00:24:40,608
I'm really sorry. I've been begging
the school for this opportunity.

376
00:24:40,686 --> 00:24:43,280
It is Lydia Haywood!

377
00:24:43,355 --> 00:24:45,289
You're gonna be great.

378
00:24:47,192 --> 00:24:48,454
Oh, God!

379
00:24:50,162 --> 00:24:51,891
Here we go.

380
00:24:51,964 --> 00:24:55,695
After all, it is the catering business,
and you never know who will be there.

381
00:24:55,768 --> 00:24:58,566
Everybody's gonna be there.
You're gonna be great.

382
00:24:58,637 --> 00:25:00,070
Salmon mousse!

383
00:25:01,907 --> 00:25:05,206
- Salmon mousse.
- Thanks.

384
00:25:05,277 --> 00:25:07,905
Mrs. Haywood.
I love your salmon mousse.

385
00:25:09,481 --> 00:25:11,472
- How is it? Good?
- I don't know.

386
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:12,983
That's good.

387
00:25:14,486 --> 00:25:18,650
Ooh, I love the way you squeeze
that mousse right in the center.

388
00:25:19,792 --> 00:25:23,228
Ooh, squeeze that mousse, baby.
Squeeze that mousse.

389
00:25:26,565 --> 00:25:28,226
What?

390
00:25:29,234 --> 00:25:30,667
What?

391
00:25:32,137 --> 00:25:34,765
- What?
- What do you have there?

392
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,967
- What is that?
- What?

393
00:25:37,042 --> 00:25:40,671
You've got something. What is that?
You okay? Burn yourself?

394
00:25:40,746 --> 00:25:42,976
Can I get a little bit of that?

395
00:25:43,048 --> 00:25:44,948
Shit! The torte tatin!

396
00:25:45,984 --> 00:25:47,417
Mitts.

397
00:25:49,855 --> 00:25:51,288
Thanks.

398
00:25:52,624 --> 00:25:55,593
- I got it.
- Clear a place. Quick. Clear a place.

399
00:25:55,661 --> 00:25:58,129
- Got it.
- Space.

400
00:25:58,197 --> 00:26:00,165
- This white one?
- My nice white tray.

401
00:26:05,037 --> 00:26:07,835
Here we go.
One, two...

402
00:26:07,906 --> 00:26:09,339
three.

403
00:26:11,977 --> 00:26:15,435
- Good job.
- Like we never stopped doing this.

404
00:26:17,282 --> 00:26:20,615
- Why are you doing that?
- 'Cause I like it.

405
00:26:20,686 --> 00:26:22,119
Come on.

406
00:26:22,187 --> 00:26:24,178
Help me take that off now.

407
00:26:26,392 --> 00:26:29,361
- Here we go. May I do the honors?
- Yes, please.

408
00:26:29,428 --> 00:26:32,295
That works.
There it goes.

409
00:26:45,711 --> 00:26:48,043
You're so beautiful.

410
00:26:48,113 --> 00:26:50,240
Give me the scissors.

411
00:26:54,753 --> 00:26:58,189
I tell you you're beautiful
and you tell me to get the scissors?

412
00:26:58,257 --> 00:27:01,226
Ouch! I gotta talk to you.

413
00:27:01,293 --> 00:27:04,228
- Gotta go.
- Gotta talk to you. Gotta talk.

414
00:27:04,296 --> 00:27:07,094
Listen to me.
I gotta talk to you.

415
00:27:07,166 --> 00:27:09,726
I gotta talk to you.
Something big's come up.

416
00:27:09,802 --> 00:27:13,431
Don't look at me that way. Something
big enough to change everything for us.

417
00:27:13,505 --> 00:27:16,201
Let me guess.
Another swell business idea...

418
00:27:16,275 --> 00:27:19,836
to invest all the money in
that you don't have.

419
00:27:19,912 --> 00:27:23,370
This is the real thing.
It's different. It's real.

420
00:27:23,449 --> 00:27:26,850
Really? Is it like
the combination salad bar...

421
00:27:26,919 --> 00:27:29,513
and Laundromat?

422
00:27:29,588 --> 00:27:32,148
Or the drive-through
teeth-cleaning place?

423
00:27:32,224 --> 00:27:35,819
What was that called?
Gary's Plaque-O-Rama.

424
00:27:35,894 --> 00:27:38,158
You even had a commercial.

425
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:40,892
Big date
Tartar problem

426
00:27:40,966 --> 00:27:44,333
That could've worked.

427
00:27:46,705 --> 00:27:50,766
That's very funny. This is
a solid thing, real, respectable.

428
00:27:50,843 --> 00:27:53,004
It's bullshit, Gary.

429
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:07,691
- You were concerned, right?
- I was very concerned.

430
00:28:07,759 --> 00:28:11,251
Pay attention to me.
I'm talking about a real thing here.

431
00:28:12,364 --> 00:28:14,127
Come on, come on.

432
00:28:14,199 --> 00:28:17,066
I've been presented with
this opportunity. It's a one-shot deal.

433
00:28:17,135 --> 00:28:19,069
It's a sure thing.

434
00:28:19,137 --> 00:28:21,196
I want to talk to you about it.
It concerns you.

435
00:28:21,273 --> 00:28:23,298
I'm not doing it anymore.
No. Good night.

436
00:28:23,375 --> 00:28:25,809
We'll chat on the way.

437
00:28:25,878 --> 00:28:27,436
Go, go, go!

438
00:28:27,513 --> 00:28:30,482
That is one messed-up couple.

439
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:33,880
The way I figure it,
this'll make us enough money...

440
00:28:33,952 --> 00:28:37,911
that if everything goes right, I could
stake you with anything you want.

441
00:28:37,990 --> 00:28:41,926
Anything your heart desires,
I can provide for you.

442
00:28:41,994 --> 00:28:43,427
That's great.

443
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:49,130
- Wish me luck.
- You don't need luck.

444
00:28:56,475 --> 00:28:58,534
One last thing.
I'm already gone.

445
00:28:58,610 --> 00:29:01,443
I wanted to let you know that scalping
tickets is history after the 25th.

446
00:29:01,513 --> 00:29:03,447
Not like the other times.

447
00:29:04,883 --> 00:29:06,316
Linda, dear.

448
00:29:07,819 --> 00:29:10,310
Who's this person?

449
00:29:10,389 --> 00:29:12,823
I'm not paying extra for help.

450
00:29:12,891 --> 00:29:15,359
- It's included.
- He's leaving.

451
00:29:15,427 --> 00:29:17,361
That's different.

452
00:29:17,429 --> 00:29:19,989
But that jacket.

453
00:29:20,065 --> 00:29:23,557
- You like it?
- No.

454
00:29:25,003 --> 00:29:26,436
Wait here.

455
00:29:27,973 --> 00:29:30,942
They loved the whatever-they-were.
Cleaned the plate.

456
00:29:31,009 --> 00:29:34,342
I'm sure the waiter's charm
had something to do with it.

457
00:29:34,413 --> 00:29:36,779
What a team.

458
00:29:50,562 --> 00:29:53,224
Linda, the salmon toast.

459
00:29:53,298 --> 00:29:56,597
I'm disappointed in their size.
They're awfully small.

460
00:29:56,668 --> 00:29:59,501
They're the standard size,
Mrs. Haywood.

461
00:29:59,571 --> 00:30:02,131
No, they were definitely small.

462
00:30:02,207 --> 00:30:05,734
We'll reflect that on the bill.

463
00:30:10,115 --> 00:30:11,548
Stop it.

464
00:30:12,618 --> 00:30:14,711
Okay, which one is hers?

465
00:30:14,786 --> 00:30:16,947
It's not worth it.

466
00:30:17,022 --> 00:30:20,583
You kidding me?
I wouldn't put up with her shit.

467
00:30:20,659 --> 00:30:22,593
You walk out, her shindig is history.

468
00:30:22,661 --> 00:30:26,961
Yeah, and I lose money and new clients
I could pick up on a job like this.

469
00:30:27,032 --> 00:30:29,466
I still say stick it to her.
It's not worth it.

470
00:30:29,534 --> 00:30:33,436
Yes, it is. I really need this.
I've got plans.

471
00:30:33,505 --> 00:30:35,837
I'm not gonna blow it over one job.

472
00:30:35,907 --> 00:30:40,935
Well, sometimes, my dear,
you just have to say "fuck it."

473
00:30:42,014 --> 00:30:43,447
Miss Haywood!

474
00:30:46,318 --> 00:30:47,751
Right.

475
00:30:52,491 --> 00:30:54,425
I'm sick of this.

476
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:03,766
Goodness, how lovely looking.

477
00:31:03,835 --> 00:31:06,463
We can only hope it tastes
as good as it looks.

478
00:31:08,006 --> 00:31:09,564
Here's your check.

479
00:31:11,209 --> 00:31:14,645
You'll find I've deducted for
the smallness of the hors d'oeuvres.

480
00:31:14,713 --> 00:31:18,171
The young man put altogether
too much champagne in the glasses.

481
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:20,718
You'll find that reflected
on the calculations.

482
00:31:20,786 --> 00:31:25,655
And Mrs. Hamlish is on a diet,
so she shouldn't count as a full person.

483
00:31:25,724 --> 00:31:30,627
A hundred dollars
doesn't even cover my expenses.

484
00:31:30,696 --> 00:31:36,032
Young lady, I've been dealing with
the Culinary Institute for many years.

485
00:31:36,101 --> 00:31:39,935
I give their best students
a grand opportunity.

486
00:31:40,005 --> 00:31:42,496
You should be paying me
for this evening.

487
00:31:42,574 --> 00:31:44,508
- Boy!
- Yes.

488
00:31:44,576 --> 00:31:47,010
- The soup!
- Coming!

489
00:31:48,213 --> 00:31:49,646
Good.

490
00:32:07,232 --> 00:32:09,166
They're applauding the chef.

491
00:32:09,234 --> 00:32:14,137
Haywood's taking all the credit.
So much for your new clients.

492
00:32:17,676 --> 00:32:20,736
I'm really sorry.
I thought you did a fantastic job.

493
00:32:24,282 --> 00:32:26,944
You did a fantastic job.
I'm proud of you.

494
00:32:27,018 --> 00:32:30,010
I agree, sometimes you do have to be
a pro in these situations.

495
00:32:30,088 --> 00:32:32,488
Sometimes you do have to make a plan
and stick to it.

496
00:32:32,557 --> 00:32:35,993
Sometimes you do have to suck it up
and eat shit.

497
00:32:37,596 --> 00:32:41,657
Sometimes... Sometimes...

498
00:32:44,836 --> 00:32:49,864
Sometimes you just gotta say
fuck it!

499
00:32:55,313 --> 00:32:57,076
Haywood time!

500
00:33:22,474 --> 00:33:23,941
I've got an idea.

501
00:33:27,412 --> 00:33:30,142
Did anybody hear the buzzer?

502
00:33:46,865 --> 00:33:49,265
Oh, how beautiful.

503
00:33:59,644 --> 00:34:02,010
I had so much fun today.

504
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:04,810
I've never done anything like that
in my whole life.

505
00:34:04,883 --> 00:34:06,373
Stop it.

506
00:34:07,586 --> 00:34:11,488
I'd love to see their faces
when they take a bite into that rawhide.

507
00:34:12,657 --> 00:34:14,557
Stop.

508
00:34:14,626 --> 00:34:16,594
Kitty litter can kill, you know.

509
00:34:20,665 --> 00:34:23,930
I've been thinking about the things
that are happening to us now.

510
00:34:27,038 --> 00:34:30,371
Did you know the pope
is coming into town?

511
00:34:30,442 --> 00:34:33,104
An event like this
could stake our future.

512
00:34:35,213 --> 00:34:37,204
I was thinking to myself...

513
00:34:37,282 --> 00:34:39,546
"What am I gonna do
with all this money?

514
00:34:39,618 --> 00:34:42,416
What are we gonna do
with all this money?"

515
00:34:42,487 --> 00:34:45,285
Because it has to be right.

516
00:34:45,357 --> 00:34:49,191
Then tonight it hits me
when I was watching you work.

517
00:34:49,261 --> 00:34:51,889
You had them eating right out
of the palm of your hand.

518
00:34:51,963 --> 00:34:54,397
Just the way you were moving.

519
00:34:54,466 --> 00:34:57,401
You're... It's like poetry.

520
00:34:57,469 --> 00:34:59,664
You're like a vision.

521
00:35:08,346 --> 00:35:10,041
What?

522
00:35:12,550 --> 00:35:13,983
Come closer.

523
00:36:39,037 --> 00:36:41,505
- Hello.
- It's Benny.

524
00:36:41,573 --> 00:36:45,532
- Call me back. I'm sleeping.
- Wake up! It's important.

525
00:36:45,610 --> 00:36:50,411
Vinnie told me Red Dog is selling
pope tickets at the Yanni concert.

526
00:36:50,482 --> 00:36:51,915
Vinnie said what?

527
00:36:51,983 --> 00:36:56,010
Pope tickets tonight. P-O-P-E.

528
00:36:56,087 --> 00:36:59,545
- How many are they releasing?
- I don't know. A lot.

529
00:36:59,624 --> 00:37:01,558
I'll be right there.

530
00:37:02,527 --> 00:37:05,223
Benny, what's happening?

531
00:37:05,296 --> 00:37:07,730
Watch your step.
Talk to me.

532
00:37:07,799 --> 00:37:12,930
You sure you don't want me to go?
Could be trouble. I can help.

533
00:37:13,004 --> 00:37:14,437
How's Stanley?

534
00:37:14,506 --> 00:37:17,532
He said his mother brought
her bridge club with her...

535
00:37:17,609 --> 00:37:19,634
so we got 22 people digging tickets.

536
00:37:19,711 --> 00:37:22,771
Stay on top of Stanley. Take Blinker
to the vet, see how she's doing.

537
00:37:22,847 --> 00:37:25,042
And I got Linda at 8:00 tonight.

538
00:37:25,116 --> 00:37:27,311
Gary, you got your ball?

539
00:37:29,287 --> 00:37:31,380
- You never know.
- Thank you, Ben.

540
00:37:33,391 --> 00:37:36,918
Gary, is that you? I need to talk
to you. Last night was...

541
00:37:36,995 --> 00:37:40,158
A mistake?
You're damn right it was.

542
00:37:40,231 --> 00:37:43,860
But don't ask me.
I'm just the nosy neighbor.

543
00:37:43,935 --> 00:37:45,368
Did you see him?

544
00:37:45,437 --> 00:37:49,032
No, but he left his love slave
a missive.

545
00:37:49,107 --> 00:37:51,041
"Off to work.
See you tonight around 8:00."

546
00:37:51,109 --> 00:37:53,475
He can't come at 8:00.
Alex is coming at 8:00.

547
00:37:53,545 --> 00:37:57,948
Like he's really gonna show up.
To Gary, "around 8:00" means next week.

548
00:37:58,016 --> 00:37:59,540
Damn!

549
00:37:59,617 --> 00:38:02,108
I wanted to tell him about Alex...

550
00:38:02,187 --> 00:38:04,485
but he kept looking at me
with those eyes.

551
00:38:04,556 --> 00:38:06,217
Those puppy-dog eyes.

552
00:38:06,291 --> 00:38:09,658
I just melt.
I have no courage.

553
00:38:09,727 --> 00:38:12,890
Lin, it came.

554
00:38:12,964 --> 00:38:15,330
Registered.
The doorman signed for it.

555
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,800
It's from Paris.

556
00:38:32,183 --> 00:38:34,117
I got in.

557
00:38:34,185 --> 00:38:35,618
Congratulations!

558
00:38:40,091 --> 00:38:42,286
When do you leave?

559
00:38:43,394 --> 00:38:46,693
Let freedom ring, Rocky. Come on.

560
00:38:46,764 --> 00:38:49,699
Nice work, Head.

561
00:38:50,568 --> 00:38:52,001
Good call.

562
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:54,903
How the fuck was I supposed to know?

563
00:38:54,973 --> 00:38:57,464
How many undercover cops
wear kilts?

564
00:39:00,979 --> 00:39:02,469
Oh, nice.

565
00:39:03,815 --> 00:39:05,248
Very nice.

566
00:39:07,018 --> 00:39:11,045
What are they gonna do to us?
I can't go to jail.

567
00:39:11,122 --> 00:39:14,114
- I don't wanna be somebody's bitch.
- Will you shut up?

568
00:39:14,192 --> 00:39:16,922
All they do is take your tickets
and hold you until the concert starts.

569
00:39:16,995 --> 00:39:21,159
Then they let you go.
You walk kind of cute, though.

570
00:39:21,232 --> 00:39:24,429
Come over here. Just sit on my lap.
I'll take care of you.

571
00:39:24,502 --> 00:39:26,800
You ever see a monkey's rear end?

572
00:39:26,871 --> 00:39:29,066
Give the guy a break.
Leave him alone.

573
00:39:29,140 --> 00:39:30,573
He's mine.

574
00:39:34,012 --> 00:39:37,072
What am I doing here?
I promised Linda I'd be back.

575
00:39:37,148 --> 00:39:38,581
Oh, Rhonda.

576
00:39:41,553 --> 00:39:43,521
What am I gonna do?

577
00:39:43,588 --> 00:39:46,751
Write a note to the guy,
tape it to the door.

578
00:39:46,824 --> 00:39:48,758
When he shows, he shows.

579
00:39:48,826 --> 00:39:50,623
Why do I do this?

580
00:39:50,695 --> 00:39:54,392
'Cause he's like a drug to you,
and you can't give him up.

581
00:39:54,465 --> 00:39:56,797
I saw that on Ricki Lake.

582
00:39:56,868 --> 00:39:58,802
This wouldn't happen
if you had a better holder.

583
00:39:58,870 --> 00:40:01,338
What Vinnie's trying to say is
Benny's too old.

584
00:40:01,406 --> 00:40:05,274
I love him, too, but he's too slow,
too fucking gone to hold.

585
00:40:05,343 --> 00:40:08,642
You gotta have somebody who can fly.
A guy like Dice McGrath...

586
00:40:08,713 --> 00:40:11,147
Skates Page, guys like that.

587
00:40:11,216 --> 00:40:12,843
They can see the oscars coming.

588
00:40:12,917 --> 00:40:15,852
How come they got your stuff,
they don't got mine?

589
00:40:17,855 --> 00:40:19,789
You know why?

590
00:40:21,259 --> 00:40:23,193
Oh, good one, Gary.

591
00:40:25,096 --> 00:40:29,624
Benny taught me that. He ain't stupid.
He gives an honest count.

592
00:40:29,701 --> 00:40:31,862
Told me he used to be
Joe Frazier's corner man.

593
00:40:31,936 --> 00:40:35,201
He told me he was one of the original
Mercury astronauts.

594
00:40:35,273 --> 00:40:38,538
I was there. I saw it.

595
00:40:38,610 --> 00:40:41,943
Frazier was fighting Young
at the Garden. I was 13 years old.

596
00:40:42,013 --> 00:40:44,174
I was working the players' entrance.

597
00:40:44,249 --> 00:40:47,741
I had six boosted ringsides in my sock.

598
00:40:47,819 --> 00:40:50,185
Three Wall Street guys come to me.

599
00:40:50,255 --> 00:40:53,918
I get 'em up to $150,
out come the shields.

600
00:40:53,992 --> 00:40:57,428
I get popped.
They threw me up against the wall.

601
00:40:57,495 --> 00:40:59,929
They started slapping me around.
Then, out of nowhere...

602
00:40:59,998 --> 00:41:02,592
comes this guy with his I.D. badge.

603
00:41:02,667 --> 00:41:06,194
He says, "The kid's clean.
The kid is with us."

604
00:41:06,271 --> 00:41:08,330
I'm going, "Who is this guy?"

605
00:41:08,406 --> 00:41:10,897
The guys let me go.
He takes me inside...

606
00:41:10,975 --> 00:41:14,411
hands me a ringside pass,
and doesn't say another word.

607
00:41:14,479 --> 00:41:16,538
I've never seen him before in my life.

608
00:41:16,614 --> 00:41:18,582
And this is Benny.

609
00:41:18,650 --> 00:41:20,675
Benjamin Moran.

610
00:41:20,752 --> 00:41:25,348
I take my ringside pass, and I'm sitting
right under Joe Frazier's corner.

611
00:41:25,423 --> 00:41:27,653
Out comes Frazier.

612
00:41:27,725 --> 00:41:31,525
Hungry! Smoking!
Next to him is?

613
00:41:31,596 --> 00:41:33,120
Benny.

614
00:41:33,197 --> 00:41:38,134
He's wearing one of those smocks
with "Smoking Joe Frazier" in sparkles.

615
00:41:38,202 --> 00:41:40,693
So he's the water boy?

616
00:41:40,772 --> 00:41:42,831
He's the corner man, asshole!

617
00:41:42,907 --> 00:41:46,365
Every time he comes back to the corner,
he's there sponging him off, saying...

618
00:41:46,444 --> 00:41:51,143
"Stay on top of him. Joe, look at me.
Don't let him breathe."

619
00:41:51,215 --> 00:41:53,376
He's doing this round after round.

620
00:41:53,451 --> 00:41:58,479
In the last round, Joe Frazier goes back
to the corner, his heart is pumping.

621
00:41:58,556 --> 00:42:02,652
Benny's screaming at the top of
his lungs, "Joe, look at me! Hook him!

622
00:42:02,727 --> 00:42:04,888
Hook him! Hook him!"

623
00:42:04,962 --> 00:42:07,954
He goes out, throws a left hook.
Boom! Fight's over.

624
00:42:08,032 --> 00:42:10,728
Great fight.
Benjamin Moran.

625
00:42:12,270 --> 00:42:14,864
That's a great story.
Too bad it's all bullshit...

626
00:42:14,939 --> 00:42:18,067
because Benny never knew
Joe Frazier.

627
00:42:19,677 --> 00:42:22,976
Want me to tell the story again?
What the fuck's going on here?

628
00:42:23,047 --> 00:42:25,675
So why'd you dump him then?

629
00:42:30,655 --> 00:42:32,850
Because he won't grow up.

630
00:42:34,325 --> 00:42:37,817
But Bug Man, I like this guy.

631
00:42:37,895 --> 00:42:40,420
He's strong, steady...

632
00:42:40,498 --> 00:42:43,092
and we get free pest control.

633
00:42:45,903 --> 00:42:48,030
Aren't you gonna get it?

634
00:43:04,288 --> 00:43:05,721
I'm coming.

635
00:43:07,992 --> 00:43:09,926
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

636
00:43:11,729 --> 00:43:15,221
What? I missed my train. Tell me
you didn't expect me until tomorrow.

637
00:43:16,100 --> 00:43:18,830
Here, I got you this.
It's that slicer on TV.

638
00:43:18,903 --> 00:43:21,804
Thanks. You gotta leave.

639
00:43:21,873 --> 00:43:23,306
Right. Okay.

640
00:43:23,374 --> 00:43:25,308
I'll take Blinker for a long walk.

641
00:43:25,376 --> 00:43:27,435
She's out for a walk.

642
00:43:32,817 --> 00:43:36,685
- Who's walking her?
- It doesn't matter.

643
00:43:36,754 --> 00:43:40,246
- It matters. Who's walking her?
- It doesn't matter. She's being walked.

644
00:43:43,561 --> 00:43:46,189
Gary, just leave it.

645
00:43:51,235 --> 00:43:55,262
- Hey, you! That's my dog!
- What?

646
00:43:55,339 --> 00:43:58,365
- Get your hands off my dog!
- This isn't your dog.

647
00:43:58,443 --> 00:44:01,276
- What are you doing with my dog?
- Taking it for a walk.

648
00:44:01,345 --> 00:44:04,439
That's what they all say.
It's not an "it," it's a "she."

649
00:44:04,515 --> 00:44:08,349
- I was taking her for a walk.
- You're trying to steal my dog.

650
00:44:08,419 --> 00:44:09,943
Wait, wait.

651
00:44:10,021 --> 00:44:14,048
Let me say one thing to you.
This isn't your dog.

652
00:44:15,159 --> 00:44:17,957
Get your hands off my dog.

653
00:44:18,029 --> 00:44:20,054
Drop the dog.

654
00:44:21,199 --> 00:44:22,461
What?

655
00:44:22,533 --> 00:44:24,660
I asked him to walk Blinker.

656
00:44:31,876 --> 00:44:34,868
Okay. You all right?

657
00:44:34,946 --> 00:44:36,880
- Sorry.
- Yeah.

658
00:44:42,086 --> 00:44:46,318
This is Alex. He's my friend.
My boyfriend.

659
00:44:50,394 --> 00:44:51,986
Look.

660
00:44:52,063 --> 00:44:54,827
I told you. I've moved on.

661
00:44:54,899 --> 00:44:57,891
I was going to tell you everything,
but you never gave me a chance.

662
00:45:09,380 --> 00:45:12,178
Hi. It's Gary.

663
00:45:12,250 --> 00:45:14,878
Linda told me all about you.

664
00:45:14,952 --> 00:45:19,252
She would've told me about you,
but I guess...

665
00:45:19,323 --> 00:45:21,257
I didn't let her.

666
00:45:21,325 --> 00:45:22,849
I screwed up.

667
00:45:27,098 --> 00:45:29,032
I should go.
Take it easy.

668
00:45:30,034 --> 00:45:31,467
See you.

669
00:45:31,536 --> 00:45:33,629
Nice meeting you.

670
00:45:45,283 --> 00:45:47,308
You ain't kidding.

671
00:45:47,385 --> 00:45:50,684
Whack the boyfriend.
He's causing you pain.

672
00:45:50,755 --> 00:45:52,882
I know a guy who'll do it as a joke.

673
00:45:52,957 --> 00:45:55,824
Make him swallow his own bug spray.

674
00:45:55,893 --> 00:45:58,293
I'm serious.
I got the guy.

675
00:45:58,362 --> 00:46:00,296
Give me the word, I'll call him.

676
00:46:00,364 --> 00:46:03,561
Sympathy is the key.

677
00:46:03,634 --> 00:46:06,034
You gotta make her
feel sorry for you.

678
00:46:06,103 --> 00:46:10,096
Get an operation.
Have something taken out of you.

679
00:46:11,242 --> 00:46:13,176
Donate one of your livers.

680
00:46:13,244 --> 00:46:17,442
You could pretend Linda's
still your girlfriend, only she's...

681
00:46:17,515 --> 00:46:20,678
away on a cruise or in a coma,
or something like that.

682
00:46:20,751 --> 00:46:23,447
Wear a sock in your pants.

683
00:46:23,521 --> 00:46:25,921
I'm serious. It works.
I've got a whole collection.

684
00:46:25,990 --> 00:46:30,086
Different sizes, lengths, thicknesses.
I'll lend you a couple. Try it.

685
00:46:30,161 --> 00:46:32,493
Get that for me, will you?

686
00:46:35,199 --> 00:46:37,997
You don't separate?

687
00:46:38,069 --> 00:46:40,367
Buy her a pair of shoes.

688
00:46:40,438 --> 00:46:42,463
Women love shoes.

689
00:46:43,274 --> 00:46:45,606
That and oral hygiene.

690
00:46:45,676 --> 00:46:49,009
Buy her a bike.
Women love bikes.

691
00:46:49,080 --> 00:46:51,674
That or a big diamond.

692
00:46:53,417 --> 00:46:56,045
She must know you have a passion.

693
00:46:56,120 --> 00:46:57,553
Tell her.

694
00:46:58,990 --> 00:47:01,322
Tell her what you feel.

695
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:12,330
Remember how she wanted me
to get a social security number?

696
00:47:12,403 --> 00:47:13,893
I should've.

697
00:47:13,971 --> 00:47:16,997
Yeah, you should've. But can he think up
a scam to fly for free?

698
00:47:17,074 --> 00:47:20,271
She doesn't care about that.
See that?

699
00:47:21,679 --> 00:47:25,979
See how the IRS has auctions
for boats and houses and stuff?

700
00:47:26,050 --> 00:47:28,382
The other day I was thinking...

701
00:47:28,452 --> 00:47:31,046
I was watching her...

702
00:47:31,122 --> 00:47:35,923
She was catering this extraordinary meal
for all these Guccis, and it hit me.

703
00:47:35,993 --> 00:47:37,961
I said, "Now I know.
I have the answer."

704
00:47:38,029 --> 00:47:41,362
The beauty of it all is that
we could do this together.

705
00:47:41,432 --> 00:47:44,458
It could be me and her
doing this together.

706
00:47:45,870 --> 00:47:47,861
That'd be great...

707
00:47:49,340 --> 00:47:52,400
being together all the time
with someone you really loved.

708
00:47:57,982 --> 00:48:00,314
You want to know
what she really wants?

709
00:48:00,384 --> 00:48:02,318
How would you know?

710
00:48:02,386 --> 00:48:05,412
I'm a girl, too,
in case you didn't notice.

711
00:48:07,191 --> 00:48:09,318
Stop talking.

712
00:48:09,393 --> 00:48:12,260
All you ever do is yak,
but what have you ever done?

713
00:48:12,329 --> 00:48:15,196
I mean something concrete.
You love her, then show her.

714
00:48:16,367 --> 00:48:19,336
- What do you think I'm doing?
- You're bullshitting.

715
00:48:22,606 --> 00:48:24,904
Do the little things.

716
00:48:24,975 --> 00:48:28,775
She wants a social security number,
then go get one. Sign some forms.

717
00:48:28,846 --> 00:48:32,748
It may not seem like much,
but it's symbolic.

718
00:48:32,817 --> 00:48:34,944
Noble deeds.

719
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:39,414
You go do that now,
and follow through...

720
00:48:39,490 --> 00:48:41,958
and maybe you've got
one last chance.

721
00:48:44,061 --> 00:48:45,494
Do it now?

722
00:48:47,832 --> 00:48:49,823
Social security number?

723
00:49:09,987 --> 00:49:13,286
Let me see what you've done
with this form, sir.

724
00:49:13,357 --> 00:49:15,825
No. You have to fill
this out completely.

725
00:49:15,893 --> 00:49:17,827
May I see your birth certificate?

726
00:49:17,895 --> 00:49:21,262
No. I couldn't find that thing.

727
00:49:21,332 --> 00:49:23,823
We need some record
that you exist...

728
00:49:23,901 --> 00:49:27,735
so I'm going to need an insurance card,
union card.

729
00:49:27,805 --> 00:49:29,238
I don't have that.

730
00:49:29,306 --> 00:49:31,433
- Voter's registration card.
- What for?

731
00:49:31,509 --> 00:49:34,273
- Bank statement.
- No.

732
00:49:34,345 --> 00:49:37,678
- Driver's license?
- No.

733
00:49:37,748 --> 00:49:39,682
I've got a locker key from the Y.

734
00:49:39,750 --> 00:49:42,344
That's not gonna help me.

735
00:49:42,419 --> 00:49:45,616
What I need is record you exist.

736
00:49:45,689 --> 00:49:48,351
It's from the Y.
Everybody knows me there.

737
00:49:48,425 --> 00:49:51,690
Step out of the line. When you have
record you exist, then come back.

738
