of looking at you slobbering
all over yourself!

976
01:07:14,615 --> 01:07:17,243
So, are you going to take
this money or not?

977
01:07:17,317 --> 01:07:20,150
Right now! One, two...

978
01:07:20,220 --> 01:07:21,653
Yes!

979
01:07:34,034 --> 01:07:39,267
Just four more days to the Papal Mass.
The city looks like Rome on the Hudson.

980
01:07:39,339 --> 01:07:43,673
You can't go anywhere without running
into someone selling pope memorabilia.

981
01:07:43,744 --> 01:07:47,043
Make a move here, Benny.

982
01:07:47,114 --> 01:07:51,483
Remind me to go by the Beacon.
You go by the "Y" and take out Blinker.

983
01:07:51,552 --> 01:07:53,918
Forget about Arty at the Broadhurst.
He's dead.

984
01:07:55,189 --> 01:07:58,647
We'll go to
Madison Square Garden someday.

985
01:07:58,725 --> 01:08:01,023
Benny, we ain't got all day.
Let's go, make a move.

986
01:08:01,094 --> 01:08:05,155
You writing this down?
Write this down. What's the matter?

987
01:08:05,232 --> 01:08:09,032
You didn't get them tickets
from no stadium guy.

988
01:08:09,102 --> 01:08:11,832
- What are you talking about?
- You got them from Fat Max.

989
01:08:11,905 --> 01:08:14,135
So what? Let's go.
Let's make a move!

990
01:08:14,208 --> 01:08:16,472
So what? He's scum!

991
01:08:16,543 --> 01:08:19,273
Who knows what he did?
Who knows where he got them?

992
01:08:19,346 --> 01:08:21,814
- Who cares?
- You used to care.

993
01:08:21,882 --> 01:08:25,750
Don't start with me.
Come on, get off my back!

994
01:08:25,819 --> 01:08:28,515
Do you want your money back?
I'll give it back.

995
01:08:28,589 --> 01:08:30,955
- You want it back?
- You know that's not it.

996
01:08:31,024 --> 01:08:33,549
Then what do you want from me?
Want me to give up on Linda?

997
01:08:33,627 --> 01:08:36,824
To give up the best thing
that's ever happened in my life?

998
01:08:36,897 --> 01:08:41,095
Don't you think I look at you every day
and pray to God I don't turn into you?

999
01:08:41,168 --> 01:08:45,468
A broken-down nobody with a bunch
of stories, half of which are bullshit.

1000
01:08:45,539 --> 01:08:48,599
But at least you have stories!

1001
01:08:48,675 --> 01:08:52,873
I got nothing, but now I got my shot.
These tickets are my way out of here.

1002
01:08:52,946 --> 01:08:57,349
I'm gonna take my shot. I've been paying
for your fuck-ups for 11 years.

1003
01:08:57,417 --> 01:08:59,908
You're no one to tell me
how to run my life.

1004
01:08:59,987 --> 01:09:03,184
Have you ever beaten anybody
in the ring?

1005
01:09:03,257 --> 01:09:05,452
Yes, I have.
And I was an honest fighter.

1006
01:09:05,525 --> 01:09:07,686
You were a human punching bag,
now you're a gofer for me.

1007
01:09:07,761 --> 01:09:12,130
Perfect. We're doing great.
What am I saying?

1008
01:09:15,068 --> 01:09:18,504
Come on, Benny, I didn't mean that.

1009
01:09:18,572 --> 01:09:21,166
- That's all right. Just keep the money.
- That's not what I meant.

1010
01:09:21,241 --> 01:09:26,110
Maybe it'll help pay for what I cost you
for the last 11 years.

1011
01:09:26,179 --> 01:09:27,840
Good-bye.
Leave me alone.

1012
01:09:32,352 --> 01:09:35,253
Benny, wait a second.
Stop, please.

1013
01:09:35,322 --> 01:09:37,313
I'm sorry I got mad at you.

1014
01:09:37,391 --> 01:09:39,359
I didn't mean what I said.

1015
01:09:39,426 --> 01:09:41,951
You're the best fighter.
You're the best corner man.

1016
01:09:42,029 --> 01:09:46,363
I just need a little room on this thing.
Just this once.

1017
01:09:46,433 --> 01:09:48,094
You said things...

1018
01:09:48,168 --> 01:09:52,127
I know. I didn't mean it.
I'm sorry. Listen to me.

1019
01:09:52,205 --> 01:09:54,673
- Look at me.
- You said things.

1020
01:09:54,741 --> 01:09:56,971
Keep your chin up here.
I gotta talk to you.

1021
01:09:57,044 --> 01:10:00,946
Stick with me. You're what separates me
from the scum of this earth.

1022
01:10:01,014 --> 01:10:04,848
You give me class.
Please stick with me on this one thing.

1023
01:10:04,918 --> 01:10:08,752
Okay? You're my corner man.
When I hurt, you stop the bleeding.

1024
01:10:08,822 --> 01:10:11,222
I'm bleeding right now,
and I need you.

1025
01:10:11,291 --> 01:10:13,816
This one time, I need you.
Please.

1026
01:10:13,894 --> 01:10:15,987
- You really need me?
- Absolutely.

1027
01:10:16,063 --> 01:10:18,224
I need you.
Please.

1028
01:10:18,298 --> 01:10:20,095
One shot.

1029
01:10:21,168 --> 01:10:23,329
If you need me, okay.

1030
01:10:23,403 --> 01:10:26,668
You're all I got, kid.

1031
01:10:26,740 --> 01:10:29,004
I got nobody else.

1032
01:11:02,909 --> 01:11:04,399
Gary!

1033
01:11:07,013 --> 01:11:09,106
All right!

1034
01:11:09,182 --> 01:11:12,811
- How you doing, man? Cool shirt!
- Where's Mrs. Paliski?

1035
01:11:12,886 --> 01:11:15,081
Over here. Come on.
Time out. Let's go.

1036
01:11:16,390 --> 01:11:19,723
I heard Linda dumped you.
Total bummer.

1037
01:11:20,727 --> 01:11:22,160
Ma!

1038
01:11:25,899 --> 01:11:30,859
I'm so happy to see you!
I was afraid you wouldn't come.

1039
01:11:30,937 --> 01:11:32,734
Free food, great broads.

1040
01:11:32,806 --> 01:11:37,505
Cut the crap. I know you.
You got something up your sleeve.

1041
01:11:37,577 --> 01:11:40,045
- Want a beer?
- Yes.

1042
01:11:41,248 --> 01:11:43,216
Look, everybody!

1043
01:11:50,323 --> 01:11:52,791
She gave you the stare.
You know what that means.

1044
01:11:52,859 --> 01:11:54,292
A long one.

1045
01:11:59,599 --> 01:12:01,362
Twice with the stare.

1046
01:12:02,569 --> 01:12:04,935
Everybody, home movies!

1047
01:12:09,976 --> 01:12:12,945
Why do we subject ourselves to this
every year? Why?

1048
01:12:13,013 --> 01:12:18,280
Why? You don't like living the most
boring moments of the past every year?

1049
01:12:19,386 --> 01:12:25,052
There's been a major technological
breakthrough. What's it called?

1050
01:12:25,125 --> 01:12:27,753
Oh, yeah. Video.

1051
01:12:27,828 --> 01:12:30,797
So you can fast forward
through all my stuff? Never.

1052
01:12:33,800 --> 01:12:36,360
Okay, here she comes.
Cut the lights.

1053
01:12:44,144 --> 01:12:46,840
This ain't Busch Gardens.

1054
01:12:46,913 --> 01:12:49,074
I was sure I put on the right reel.

1055
01:12:49,149 --> 01:12:51,344
It's Gary and Linda.

1056
01:12:51,418 --> 01:12:53,682
You got it out of focus.

1057
01:12:53,753 --> 01:12:56,187
Leave it. We want to see this.

1058
01:12:58,592 --> 01:13:02,528
When did Blinky develop
that skin rash?

1059
01:13:02,596 --> 01:13:04,757
You guys make a lovely couple.

1060
01:13:10,070 --> 01:13:12,800
Oh, what a couple!

1061
01:13:18,545 --> 01:13:19,978
Good work.

1062
01:13:59,953 --> 01:14:02,080
I knew you'd be here.

1063
01:14:02,155 --> 01:14:05,318
- You embarrassed me.
- I know. I'm sorry.

1064
01:14:05,392 --> 01:14:08,884
I just wanted to give you
this little not-going-away present.

1065
01:14:11,398 --> 01:14:13,696
I found it in one of my bags.

1066
01:14:13,767 --> 01:14:16,099
It's a trophy.

1067
01:14:17,170 --> 01:14:22,608
This is what's important.
It's a first-place couples competition.

1068
01:14:22,676 --> 01:14:25,770
Remember?
We won it at Macy's picnic.

1069
01:14:25,845 --> 01:14:28,814
We won the three-legged race...

1070
01:14:28,882 --> 01:14:32,318
the tag-team sack race
and the egg pushing contest.

1071
01:14:32,385 --> 01:14:35,684
- Want to know why?
- 'Cause we weren't drinking.

1072
01:14:37,157 --> 01:14:39,489
No. Because we were
the best couple together.

1073
01:14:39,559 --> 01:14:42,426
Best first-place couple.

1074
01:14:42,495 --> 01:14:45,089
Best together.
Me and you.

1075
01:14:45,165 --> 01:14:50,660
I'm working on something that will
resolve your problems. Listen to me.

1076
01:14:50,737 --> 01:14:54,696
Don't you ever get tired
of dreaming?

1077
01:14:54,774 --> 01:14:57,675
Ever since we met, you've dreamed
of wonderful things for us.

1078
01:14:57,744 --> 01:15:03,444
Things that have made my heart soar.
But what do we have to show for it?

1079
01:15:03,516 --> 01:15:06,610
- What?
- Let me show you.

1080
01:15:08,388 --> 01:15:12,085
I loved you like I have loved no other,
and believed in you with all my heart.

1081
01:15:12,158 --> 01:15:15,559
But I need to know what is gonna happen
with the rest of my life.

1082
01:15:15,629 --> 01:15:17,290
Give me two weeks...

1083
01:15:17,364 --> 01:15:19,525
and I'll show you.

1084
01:15:30,744 --> 01:15:32,735
I'm gonna miss you.

1085
01:15:38,685 --> 01:15:42,553
Okay, a week. One week!

1086
01:15:46,459 --> 01:15:49,326
Hi, sweetie. How are you?

1087
01:15:49,396 --> 01:15:51,990
- Great!
- Mind if I join you?

1088
01:15:52,065 --> 01:15:56,434
Please. I'd love the company.
Want a bite?

1089
01:15:56,503 --> 01:15:59,961
No. I don't like
to mix my meats.

1090
01:16:00,040 --> 01:16:03,498
That looks too rich.
Been having a little indigestion lately.

1091
01:16:03,576 --> 01:16:05,601
I wonder why.

1092
01:16:05,679 --> 01:16:08,910
It's not the dogs.
It's the chemicals.

1093
01:16:10,817 --> 01:16:12,751
It's really nice to see you.

1094
01:16:12,819 --> 01:16:15,947
What brings you to the neighborhood?
Do you have business?

1095
01:16:16,022 --> 01:16:20,618
No. I just wanna talk to you
about Gary.

1096
01:16:20,694 --> 01:16:22,889
There's nothing left to say.

1097
01:16:24,431 --> 01:16:27,764
Do you see what it's been like for him
these years with nobody?

1098
01:16:29,135 --> 01:16:32,935
I know he doesn't have a family.
I brought him into mine.

1099
01:16:33,006 --> 01:16:35,634
I wanted to start a family with him.

1100
01:16:35,709 --> 01:16:40,737
Look. Do you think leaving him
is easy? It's not.

1101
01:16:43,983 --> 01:16:47,316
You're everything to him.
You're his angel.

1102
01:16:52,792 --> 01:16:56,990
He's onto something,
and I don't know what.

1103
01:16:57,063 --> 01:17:01,432
But he's onto something,
and it's important.

1104
01:17:05,405 --> 01:17:09,808
There's a different look in his eyes.
I never saw it before.

1105
01:17:09,876 --> 01:17:12,174
There's a burning in there.

1106
01:17:12,245 --> 01:17:15,874
It's intense.

1107
01:17:15,949 --> 01:17:18,747
It's a determination, like a focus.

1108
01:17:18,818 --> 01:17:23,585
You'll see what I'm talking about,
because it's there.

1109
01:17:23,656 --> 01:17:25,180
I want...

1110
01:17:26,826 --> 01:17:30,057
I'm gonna ask you
to do something for me.

1111
01:17:31,264 --> 01:17:33,425
It'll make this old man feel like...

1112
01:17:33,500 --> 01:17:39,166
he's finally done something meaningful
later on in his life.

1113
01:17:39,239 --> 01:17:41,969
Will you promise me something?

1114
01:17:42,942 --> 01:17:46,343
No, no. This is not
what my partner and I had in mind.

1115
01:17:46,412 --> 01:17:50,439
-You'll have to swing two years on that.
-We're looking for five.

1116
01:17:50,517 --> 01:17:53,452
You'll have to swing two,
and you got till Monday.

1117
01:17:53,520 --> 01:17:56,455
There's another buyer interested.

1118
01:17:57,791 --> 01:18:01,158
No, there's not.
I'll see you Monday.

1119
01:18:20,914 --> 01:18:22,404
Benny!

1120
01:18:27,420 --> 01:18:30,218
Benny, let's go.
Let's make a move.

1121
01:18:30,290 --> 01:18:32,349
Three more days to show time!

1122
01:18:32,425 --> 01:18:35,189
Come on, let's go. Benny.

1123
01:20:18,264 --> 01:20:19,891
This is it?

1124
01:20:19,966 --> 01:20:23,367
Yes. It's a lovely spot!
Isn't it?

1125
01:20:32,912 --> 01:20:35,881
How much for something
with a little privacy?

1126
01:20:46,693 --> 01:20:48,354
This way.

1127
01:20:52,432 --> 01:20:55,890
Level, dickhead. Pick it up!

1128
01:20:55,969 --> 01:20:57,994
I got the heavy end.

1129
01:21:11,317 --> 01:21:13,581
Sister Betrayal, English, please.

1130
01:21:15,588 --> 01:21:19,183
- Some lives begin with birth.
- Some?

1131
01:21:19,258 --> 01:21:21,226
Some?

1132
01:21:22,228 --> 01:21:24,924
Others take flight.

1133
01:21:24,998 --> 01:21:26,260
Be quiet.

1134
01:21:26,332 --> 01:21:29,426
Faster, Father.

1135
01:21:29,502 --> 01:21:32,232
Guys, give him a break.
He's trying to do his job.

1136
01:21:32,305 --> 01:21:35,172
Lose the priest. Padre,
go get yourself a whiskey sour.

1137
01:21:35,241 --> 01:21:38,335
Gary, you say something about him.
You knew him best.

1138
01:21:38,411 --> 01:21:40,402
Yeah, right, Gary.

1139
01:21:41,447 --> 01:21:43,642
Nice try. Tough crowd.

1140
01:21:51,457 --> 01:21:53,755
A lot of things
I could say about Benny.

1141
01:21:53,826 --> 01:21:56,852
He liked you guys a lot.

1142
01:21:59,465 --> 01:22:02,457
Nobody played a cripple
better than Benny.

1143
01:22:02,535 --> 01:22:03,968
That's true.

1144
01:22:04,037 --> 01:22:05,629
For sure.

1145
01:22:09,809 --> 01:22:12,039
Excuse me.

1146
01:22:14,247 --> 01:22:16,044
Excuse us.

1147
01:22:33,866 --> 01:22:36,266
- You Gary?
- Yes, sir.

1148
01:22:36,335 --> 01:22:37,927
Thanks for calling.

1149
01:22:39,072 --> 01:22:41,302
Thanks for coming, Champ.

1150
01:22:43,509 --> 01:22:45,443
Hook 'em, Benny!

1151
01:22:45,511 --> 01:22:47,069
Thank you.

1152
01:22:51,918 --> 01:22:54,352
Hey, Joe,
I was Benny's best friend.

1153
01:22:54,420 --> 01:22:56,911
Sorry, Benny.
I thought it was all bullshit.

1154
01:22:56,989 --> 01:22:58,980
Let's go get an autograph.

1155
01:23:09,235 --> 01:23:12,864
Benny was lucky to have you
in his life.

1156
01:23:14,874 --> 01:23:17,399
You meant the world to him.

1157
01:23:22,014 --> 01:23:23,948
Look at this.

1158
01:23:30,623 --> 01:23:32,955
You want a ride to the city?

1159
01:23:40,600 --> 01:23:43,091
I wanna stay here for a while.

1160
01:23:54,981 --> 01:23:56,414
What is it?

1161
01:23:57,783 --> 01:24:00,013
It's there!

1162
01:24:00,887 --> 01:24:03,014
What does that mean?

1163
01:24:04,357 --> 01:24:08,657
Benny came to see me the other day and
said you were going to ask me something.

1164
01:24:08,728 --> 01:24:13,097
And that no matter what it was,
I was to say "yes."

1165
01:24:13,166 --> 01:24:16,135
To do that for him.

1166
01:24:23,442 --> 01:24:28,607
Okay. Will you meet me
some place Monday at 9:00 a.m.?

1167
01:24:31,150 --> 01:24:36,918
It'll be the last thing I ask of you.
Monday, 9:00 a.m., 157 Duane Street.

1168
01:24:38,057 --> 01:24:39,752
Please, for Benny.

1169
01:24:43,362 --> 01:24:45,592
Not just for Benny.

1170
01:24:47,166 --> 01:24:48,599
For you.

1171
01:25:00,880 --> 01:25:04,145
Tomorrow's the big day.
Papal Mass at Yankee Stadium.

1172
01:25:14,026 --> 01:25:15,550
Can I come in?

1173
01:25:15,628 --> 01:25:20,031
No. And I ain't got
any money for you.

1174
01:25:21,500 --> 01:25:24,799
Fat Max got arrested yesterday.

1175
01:25:24,870 --> 01:25:28,636
Those tickets you got,
they were for...

1176
01:25:28,708 --> 01:25:33,145
some church thing, some charity thing
and they're looking for you.

1177
01:25:37,817 --> 01:25:41,685
The heat's really heavy on this.

1178
01:26:03,209 --> 01:26:05,177
Don't cry, please.

1179
01:26:05,244 --> 01:26:07,178
Don't cry. Okay?

1180
01:26:08,748 --> 01:26:10,682
Listen to me.

1181
01:26:10,750 --> 01:26:14,652
I know a Dr. Perlman.
He's a good friend. I sell him tickets.

1182
01:26:14,720 --> 01:26:17,621
I'm gonna take you there tomorrow,
and we're gonna get you all better.

1183
01:26:17,690 --> 01:26:20,625
And clean you up.
And this baby's gonna be fine.

1184
01:26:23,763 --> 01:26:27,665
You ever hear that
it's good for kids to listen to music?

1185
01:26:30,169 --> 01:26:31,898
Wanna see?

1186
01:26:34,073 --> 01:26:36,769
- Wait. Wait.
- You don't want to?

1187
01:26:36,842 --> 01:26:39,936
No, I'm just scared.

1188
01:26:40,012 --> 01:26:41,445
Wait.

1189
01:26:47,520 --> 01:26:49,715
That's beautiful.

1190
01:26:59,031 --> 01:27:02,694
Earl "The Pearl" Monroe.
He's goin'! He's movin'!

1191
01:27:02,768 --> 01:27:08,263
He's got it. Turning the ball over.
Going for the jump shot.

1192
01:27:11,210 --> 01:27:16,546
Let's put this on. Where's the head?
That's the head there?

1193
01:27:39,138 --> 01:27:42,107
Good morning, New York!
The big day has arrived.

1194
01:27:42,174 --> 01:27:45,473
The Papal Mass at Yankee Stadium
in four hours.

1195
01:28:22,548 --> 01:28:25,813
Forgive me, Father,
for I am about to sin.

1196
01:29:07,626 --> 01:29:11,460
Come on, folks. Tickets, 900 a pop.

1197
01:29:11,530 --> 01:29:13,589
It's once in a lifetime.

1198
01:29:13,666 --> 01:29:15,600
This is genuine Popesicles...

1199
01:29:15,668 --> 01:29:19,365
made with Vatican sugar
and holy water.

1200
01:29:19,438 --> 01:29:22,498
T-shirts.
New from the Vatican collection.

1201
01:29:22,575 --> 01:29:25,373
Pope T-shirts.
He's back, he's here!

1202
01:29:27,379 --> 01:29:31,008
This is the big score. He wasn't
at the apartment. He's gotta be here.

1203
01:29:31,083 --> 01:29:33,381
The guy is here.

1204
01:29:33,452 --> 01:29:35,716
- Thank you very much.
- Did you see Gary?

1205
01:29:35,788 --> 01:29:39,747
He's not gonna be here.
With all these people around? No way.

1206
01:29:39,825 --> 01:29:43,420
A lot of oscars here.
I hope he stays low. Pope T-shirts.

1207
01:30:02,348 --> 01:30:07,684
Excuse me, Sister.
This guy is looking for a pair.

1208
01:30:07,753 --> 01:30:11,450
You got $600? Box seats.
Right behind first base.

1209
01:30:12,424 --> 01:30:15,018
One, two, three, four, five, six.
Let's go.

1210
01:30:15,094 --> 01:30:17,153
Bless you, my son.

1211
01:30:18,163 --> 01:30:20,097
- How are we doing?
- Very nice.

1212
01:30:20,165 --> 01:30:22,190
Say some Hail Marys.
We might pull this off.

1213
01:30:22,268 --> 01:30:25,066
- Been there, done that.
- See ya.

1214
01:30:25,137 --> 01:30:29,073
Tickets? Close enough
to count the beads.

1215
01:30:32,878 --> 01:30:34,311
$500.

1216
01:30:41,720 --> 01:30:44,655
You got tickets?
What do you need? Two?

1217
01:30:44,723 --> 01:30:47,055
The oscars.

1218
01:30:48,294 --> 01:30:51,991
Right there.
Knock yourself out.

1219
01:30:52,064 --> 01:30:54,862
A lady and a lucky man.
I'll say a prayer for you.

1220
01:30:57,069 --> 01:31:00,937
He's dressed up. The guy's here.
I'm telling you. He's everywhere.

1221
01:31:01,006 --> 01:31:05,170
There's no way he couldn't be here.
Hey, give me a break.

1222
01:31:07,413 --> 01:31:09,472
Tickets? Tickets?

1223
01:31:10,549 --> 01:31:14,679
Very clever.
That's very, very clever.

1224
01:31:14,753 --> 01:31:18,189
You almost pulled this off.
Almost.

1225
01:31:18,257 --> 01:31:20,350
The dance is over, my friend.

1226
01:31:21,493 --> 01:31:24,860
Police! Police!
It's him! That's him!

1227
01:31:30,102 --> 01:31:31,865
Over here.

1228
01:32:37,002 --> 01:32:39,232
He say anything?

1229
01:32:41,206 --> 01:32:45,040
I'm here to ask you one more time.

1230
01:32:45,110 --> 01:32:47,670
Where are those tickets?

1231
01:33:00,826 --> 01:33:03,192
I don't know anything
about any tickets.

1232
01:33:08,200 --> 01:33:11,260
He's lying.
We'll get him.

1233
01:33:57,816 --> 01:34:00,614
Knock 'em dead, Pope.

1234
01:34:00,686 --> 01:34:02,711
Knock 'em dead.

1235
01:34:11,163 --> 01:34:14,360
You've been blessed. Now get out.

1236
01:34:47,232 --> 01:34:48,824
Hey, brother.

1237
01:34:52,237 --> 01:34:56,139
What happened today, all that commotion
you had to go through...

1238
01:34:57,309 --> 01:34:59,470
was 'cause of me.

1239
01:35:01,046 --> 01:35:04,914
Remember when I told you
this was the wild west?

1240
01:35:04,983 --> 01:35:06,575
Well...

1241
01:35:06,652 --> 01:35:09,644
I'm the one with all the horses
and I got all the land.

1242
01:35:09,721 --> 01:35:13,748
You want to work on my land,
you have to pay the baron's price.

1243
01:35:13,826 --> 01:35:15,726
Works like this.

1244
01:35:15,794 --> 01:35:21,357
I supply tickets and protection
for 70% of your take.

1245
01:35:24,903 --> 01:35:29,203
Okay. Why don't you
go fuck yourself?

1246
01:35:32,311 --> 01:35:34,074
Piece of shit!

1247
01:35:42,321 --> 01:35:44,949
Hold him up. Hold him up.

1248
01:35:45,023 --> 01:35:47,184
Hold him up.

1249
01:35:47,259 --> 01:35:49,727
Like that? Like that shit?

1250
01:35:50,963 --> 01:35:54,922
That's for calling me coconut,
you fuck! Let's go.

1251
01:35:55,000 --> 01:35:57,025
Let's go.

1252
01:35:57,102 --> 01:35:58,535
Shit!

1253
01:36:04,009 --> 01:36:05,442
Gary?

1254
01:36:06,945 --> 01:36:10,642
- Are you all right?
- Let me help you up.

1255
01:36:12,217 --> 01:36:14,549
- You all right?
- He's all bloody.

1256
01:36:14,620 --> 01:36:17,384
Shit. Come on.

1257
01:36:17,456 --> 01:36:19,651
Oh. Oh, man.

1258
01:36:21,994 --> 01:36:25,987
- I got it.
- You all right?

1259
01:36:26,064 --> 01:36:29,261
- I got it, I got it.
- All right.

1260
01:36:29,334 --> 01:36:32,360
- Slow down. Hold on.
- Easy. You aren't going anywhere.

1261
01:36:32,437 --> 01:36:35,099
I'm okay. I got it.

1262
01:36:38,877 --> 01:36:41,072
Where are you going?
Come on, hang on.

1263
01:36:41,146 --> 01:36:43,808
Hey, I don't work here no more.

1264
01:38:20,679 --> 01:38:24,376
Yes, Mr. Starke? I'm Ray Charles
from Farmer's Insurance.

1265
01:38:25,584 --> 01:38:27,575
Mr. Starke, sir?

1266
01:38:30,455 --> 01:38:32,946
- What?
- I know. I get that all the time.

1267
01:38:33,025 --> 01:38:36,324
I'm obviously not that Ray Charles.
But I'm not here to sell you insurance.

1268
01:38:36,395 --> 01:38:39,387
May I come in just a moment?

1269
01:38:40,866 --> 01:38:43,391
Just take a moment of your time.

1270
01:38:46,138 --> 01:38:49,596
I just have a couple questions
for you on this whole thing.

1271
01:38:49,674 --> 01:38:52,336
Obviously...

1272
01:38:52,411 --> 01:38:54,777
you are the...

1273
01:38:54,846 --> 01:38:58,111
Gary Starke who resides
at 215 West 23rd Street.

1274
01:39:00,719 --> 01:39:02,152
Yeah.

1275
01:39:03,288 --> 01:39:05,984
Good. Now as...

1276
01:39:06,058 --> 01:39:09,892
Mr. Moran's sole beneficiary
on the life insurance policy...

1277
01:39:09,961 --> 01:39:15,058
what I need to do is get a couple
of paperwork things finished up.

1278
01:39:15,133 --> 01:39:17,829
What did you say there?

1279
01:39:17,903 --> 01:39:19,803
Benjamin Moran.

1280
01:39:19,871 --> 01:39:22,999
He has you listed as the beneficiary
on his life insurance policy.

1281
01:39:24,142 --> 01:39:27,737
We've been looking for you
for almost a week.

1282
01:39:27,813 --> 01:39:32,773
I don't usually find it so hard
to give away $56,000.

1283
01:39:32,851 --> 01:39:34,580
Tax free.

1284
01:39:37,355 --> 01:39:40,415
If I can see some identification.

1285
01:39:52,270 --> 01:39:55,364
I don't have any identification.

1286
01:39:59,211 --> 01:40:01,145
That is correct.

1287
01:40:01,213 --> 01:40:05,946
It says the recipient should have
no means of identification.

1288
01:40:06,017 --> 01:40:09,316
In which case, Mr. Starke...

1289
01:40:09,387 --> 01:40:13,881
I can give you this, sir.

1290
01:40:13,959 --> 01:40:16,985
If I can just
leave this with you.

1291
01:40:17,062 --> 01:40:20,190
And I almost forgot.
Bear with me.

1292
01:40:20,265 --> 01:40:25,635
The City Probate Office asked me
to forward this to you.

1293
01:40:25,704 --> 01:40:27,331
I said I would.

1294
01:40:27,405 --> 01:40:30,738
That's for you as well.

1295
01:40:30,809 --> 01:40:34,404
I do wish you a very good day.

1296
01:40:34,479 --> 01:40:36,709
Good luck to you, sir.

1297
01:40:36,781 --> 01:40:40,410
Have a really fine day, sir.
Good-bye.

1298
01:41:19,791 --> 01:41:21,622
All there.

1299
01:41:27,299 --> 01:41:29,995
Benny! Yes!

1300
01:41:31,036 --> 01:41:32,731
Linda?

1301
01:41:33,972 --> 01:41:36,907
Linda, I'm coming.

1302
01:41:44,916 --> 01:41:47,544
Open up.
I know you don't leave till tomorrow.

1303
01:41:47,619 --> 01:41:50,247
Sorry. Where's Linda?

1304
01:41:50,322 --> 01:41:52,085
Linda's gone.

1305
01:41:53,258 --> 01:41:57,422
I'm the new tenant. I'm Vickie.
Who are you?

1306
01:42:00,398 --> 01:42:03,299
Rhonda. Rhonda.
It's me Gary. Open up.

1307
01:42:03,368 --> 01:42:05,131
- What?
- Where is she?

1308
01:42:05,203 --> 01:42:07,262
I don't have to tell you anything.

1309
01:42:07,339 --> 01:42:11,070
Please open the door.
Please open the door. One time.

1310
01:42:13,178 --> 01:42:18,013
- I beg of you. Tell me where'd she go.
- Why should I tell you anything?

1311
01:42:18,083 --> 01:42:22,144
I want to do this one thing for her.
Just one thing. Please.

1312
01:42:23,688 --> 01:42:28,489
She at her mom's. But you're too late.
They're on their way to the airport.

1313
01:42:29,561 --> 01:42:30,823
Good luck.

1314
01:42:30,895 --> 01:42:34,991
Mrs. Paliski?
Yeah, this is Gary.

1315
01:42:35,066 --> 01:42:38,832
Listen. No, everything's fine.
I need you to do me a favor.

1316
01:42:44,109 --> 01:42:47,476
Which way are you going?

1317
01:42:47,545 --> 01:42:50,742
Honey, let the man do his job.

1318
01:42:50,815 --> 01:42:53,511
But I said Kennedy.

1319
01:42:53,585 --> 01:42:56,053
You missed the tunnel.
Can you turn back?

1320
01:42:56,121 --> 01:42:57,645
Relax.

1321
01:43:00,292 --> 01:43:03,318
That's it. I'm writing down
your badge number.

1322
01:43:05,697 --> 01:43:10,794
The old broad gave me a fifty to take
you to this corner and drop you off.

1323
01:43:10,869 --> 01:43:13,394
For fifty more, I will take you
wherever you want to go.

1324
01:43:13,471 --> 01:43:16,463
- I'm not giving you a dime.
- Then get out!

1325
01:43:23,214 --> 01:43:25,239
I don't know what is going on.

1326
01:43:25,317 --> 01:43:28,582
I don't know.
I just like the guy.

1327
01:43:28,653 --> 01:43:31,349
And if I'm wrong,
you'll just have to forgive me.

1328
01:43:36,061 --> 01:43:38,029
Taxi! Yo!

1329
01:46:02,674 --> 01:46:04,164
Come with me.

1330
01:46:06,511 --> 01:46:08,672
Three. Table seven.

1331
01:46:27,899 --> 01:46:31,596
Service charge is included.
Go in peace, Gary.

1332
01:46:31,669 --> 01:46:34,399
Thank you, Father.
In peace I go.

1333
01:46:42,180 --> 01:46:46,116
Honey, have you noticed
we are $200 to $300 over every night?

1334
01:46:46,184 --> 01:46:47,344
Really?

1335
01:46:47,418 --> 01:46:49,784
Do you have any idea why?

1336
01:46:49,854 --> 01:46:51,378
Not a clue.

1337
01:46:51,456 --> 01:46:55,984
Really? Could you take the pot
and follow me?

1338
01:47:15,013 --> 01:47:19,143
Gary, let it go. Leave it.

1339
01:47:21,286 --> 01:47:23,811
Save the paper.

1340
01:54:24,742 --> 01:54:27,472
Five dollars, five dollars.

1341
01:54:32,049 --> 01:54:34,040
Five dollars, ma'am.
Five dollars, huh?

1342
01:54:35,186 --> 01:54:37,586
Nice haircut.
What size bowl they use?

1343
01:54:41,325 --> 01:54:43,452
You can't hear it,
but your dog can.

1344
01:54:43,527 --> 01:54:45,859
Five dollars, brother.
How 'bout...

1345
01:54:47,298 --> 01:54:49,095
Four dollars.

1346
01:54:49,166 --> 01:54:51,896
Four fifty.
Then forget it.

